item.description:
The Massachusetts Republican State Committee will elect at-large delegates and alternates to the National Convention in St. Paul next Tuesday at this meeting. Though there will no candidates running under a 'Ron Paul' banner (only delegates for Romney and McCain are in order) several individuals who support constitutional government will throw their hats into the ring.

Please come and show your support for these individuals and have a positive dialogue with members of the Republican State Committee on the future of the GOP.

May 13 at the Crowne Plaza, 1360 Worcester Street, Rt. 9, Natick, MA
01760. It starts at 7:00 pm.

For more information or if you would like to help prepare for the election:
Joe Ureneck:
jureneck@comcast.net
857 350-0575
item.name: Election of At-large Delegates to Republican National Convention
